{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make a rule that all restaurants have to have menus available without calories.",
        "additional_details": "I am recovering from an eating disorder. I\u2019ve had one since I was twelve years old, and when I go out to eat, I see the calories on every menu. On every site to order food. It makes eating really difficult, and I wish there were menus without calories people in recovery, or people who don\u2019t want to know, could look at, to feel safe and secure when they eat. I would benefit from this, and I believe many other people would, too.",
        "background": "I want the UK Government to consider making it a rule that restaurants have to have menus available without calorie counts to prevent distress for people that are in eating disorder recovery.",
